  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for ffmpeg-4",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for ffmpeg-4 fixes the following issues:\n\nChanges in ffmpeg-4:\n\n- Add check for the return value of av_malloc_array() to avoid potential NULL pointer dereference.  (CVE-2025-10256, bsc#1249431)\n\n- Update to version 4.4.7:\n  * Codecs, filters and other various bugfixes\n  * aacenc_tns: clamp filter direction energy measurement.  (CVE-2025-1594, bsc#1237561)\n  * avcodec/jpeg2000dec: implement cdef remapping during pixel format matching.  (CVE-2025-9951, bsc#1249393)\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
